OL,3,CA fifth of people deemed at risk of
OL,4,Cpoverty in eight-year period, says
OL,5,Cstudy
OL,7,FOn average, 22% of the population
OL,8,Fexperienced deprivation at least once
OL,9,Fin two consecutive years from 2016 to
OL,10,F2023: almost half of these were in
OL,11,Fpersistent deprivation, slightly less
OL,12,Fthan a third were exiting deprivation
OL,13,Fand about a quarter were entering
OL,14,Fdeprivation.
OL,16,FThe study noted that there was a post-
OL,17,Fpandemic spike observed amongst lone-
OL,18,Fparent families, 30 to 65-year-old
OL,19,Fsingle people, adults above 65, and
OL,20,Fespecially amongst single people over
OL,21,F65.
