OL,3,CA fifth of people deemed at risk of
OL,4,Cpoverty in eight-year period, says
OL,5,Cstudy
OL,7,FIt found that the annual at-risk-of-
OL,8,Fpoverty (AROP) rate declined from 16%
OL,9,Fin 2016 to 11% in 2023, while the
OL,10,Fpersistent AROP rate declined from 10%
OL,11,Fin 2015-2016 to 7% in 2022-2023.
OL,13,FThe latter shows the share of the
OL,14,Fpopulation who were AROP two years in
OL,15,Fa row.
OL,17,FMaterial deprivation increased in the
OL,18,Frecent period from 14% in 2021 to 17%
OL,19,Fin 2023.
