OL,3,CA fifth of people deemed at risk of
OL,4,Cpoverty in eight-year period, says
OL,5,Cstudy
OL,7,FOver the period 2016 to 2023, an
OL,8,Faverage of 5% of people were both AROP
OL,9,Fand deprived.
OL,11,FLone parent families, large families,
OL,12,Fand households with a working-age
OL,13,Fadult with a disability faced the
OL,14,Fhighest risks of persistent AROP and
OL,15,Fdeprivation, it said.
OL,17,FChildren in lone parent families, in
OL,18,Fparticular, are most at risk, with an
OL,19,Faverage 33% of them being persistently
OL,20,Fdeprived, and 21% being persistently
OL,21,FAROP, between 2016 and 2023.
